{"name":"Volition Base Rules","content":"<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The Campaign</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">In the game of Volition, a Gamemaster (GM) creates a world with Non-Player Characters (NPCs), and the players create Player Characters (PCs).  Then, the GM brings the PCs together in the world, and the PCs take actions to create a story. The GM introduces obstacles of different forms to the PCs, who either overcome them using skills or fail to overcome them and potentially take damage. Over time, the PCs earn experience, which they can use to enhance their skills. Eventually, the PCs accomplish their goals, or fail to accomplish their goals and become retired, leaving the story to be replaced by a new PC. This is a campaign.</span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Dice</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">To play Volition, each player (and the GM) must have a set of polyhedral dice, one for each in the list below (except d1). Dice are denoted in these rules by the letter “d” followed by the number of sides on the die. For example, a d4 is a four-sided die and a d12 is a twelve-sided die.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-73a29f92-7fff-920f-6152-5cfcb5c29974\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Often, the rules will refer to increasing or decreasing the size of a die. To increase a die, move one size to the right on the list below. To decrease a die, move one size to the left on the list below. Dice cannot be increased above d20 or decreased below d1. No physical die is needed when rolling a d1; just treat the result as “1.”</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">d1 &gt; d4 &gt; d6 &gt; d8 &gt; d10 &gt; d12 &gt; d20</span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Hits and Misses</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Whenever you roll a die, the only thing that matters is whether the result is 4 or greater. If it is, the roll is a “hit.” If the result is 3 or lower, the roll is a “miss.” Rolling a d1 always results in a miss. What exactly happens when you roll a hit or miss will depend on the circumstances and rules that led to you rolling the dice, as well as any other dice that are rolled and their results.  </span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Rounding and Subtraction </span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sometimes you need to divide a whole number in half. If the result would be a decimal, always round up. For example, if you would take 5 damage, but a skill lets you halve the damage taken, instead take 3 damage. </span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">If something would reduce a number, the number cannot be reduced below zero. If you have 2 HP remaining and take 4 damage, your new HP is 0, not -2. Similarly, if you have 3 armor, which reduces damage by the amount of armor, and you take 2 damage, the damage is reduced to 0, not -1. </span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Stacking Effects</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A character can only be affected by one instance of the same skill, power, item, or condition at a time. For example, the Shieldmaster skill grants +1 armor while holding a shield, but holding two shields does not grant any additional armor. If you go 24 hours without sleep, you become exhausted, but another 24 hours without sleep does not make you doubly exhausted. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> </span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.S9oUeafdAW2i9LWP"}},"_id":"NkkWRrleRum0o6Ag"}
{"_id":"NkkWRrleRum0o6Ag","name":"Volition Base Rules","content":"<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The Campaign</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">In the game of Volition, a Gamemaster (GM) creates a world with Non-Player Characters (NPCs), and the players create Player Characters (PCs).  Then, the GM brings the PCs together in the world, and the PCs take actions to create a story. The GM introduces obstacles of different forms to the PCs, who either overcome them using skills or fail to overcome them and potentially take damage. Over time, the PCs earn experience, which they can use to enhance their skills. Eventually, the PCs accomplish their goals, or fail to accomplish their goals and become retired, leaving the story to be replaced by a new PC. This is a campaign.</span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Dice</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">To play Volition, each player (and the GM) must have a set of polyhedral dice, one for each in the list below (except d1). Dice are denoted in these rules by the letter “d” followed by the number of sides on the die. For example, a d4 is a four-sided die and a d12 is a twelve-sided die.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-73a29f92-7fff-920f-6152-5cfcb5c29974\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Often, the rules will refer to increasing or decreasing the size of a die. To increase a die, move one size to the right on the list below. To decrease a die, move one size to the left on the list below. Dice cannot be increased above d20 or decreased below d1. No physical die is needed when rolling a d1; just treat the result as “1.”</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">d1 &gt; d4 &gt; d6 &gt; d8 &gt; d10 &gt; d12 &gt; d20</span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Hits and Misses</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Whenever you roll a die, the only thing that matters is whether the result is 4 or greater. If it is, the roll is a “hit.” If the result is 3 or lower, the roll is a “miss.” Rolling a d1 always results in a miss. What exactly happens when you roll a hit or miss will depend on the circumstances and rules that led to you rolling the dice, as well as any other dice that are rolled and their results.  </span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Rounding and Subtraction </span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sometimes you need to divide a whole number in half. If the result would be a decimal, always round up. For example, if you would take 5 damage, but a skill lets you halve the damage taken, instead take 3 damage. </span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">If something would reduce a number, the number cannot be reduced below zero. If you have 2 HP remaining and take 4 damage, your new HP is 0, not -2. Similarly, if you have 3 armor, which reduces damage by the amount of armor, and you take 2 damage, the damage is reduced to 0, not -1. </span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Stacking Effects</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A character can only be affected by one instance of the same skill, power, item, or condition at a time. For example, the Shieldmaster skill grants +1 armor while holding a shield, but holding two shields does not grant any additional armor. If you go 24 hours without sleep, you become exhausted, but another 24 hours without sleep does not make you doubly exhausted. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> </span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.S9oUeafdAW2i9LWP"}}}
{"name":"Your Player Character","content":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">As a player, you control a Player Character (PC) who is one of the main characters in the story that you, the GM, and the other players are writing together. Your PC is a unique individual with their own feelings, goals, ideas, and flaws. This section describes different aspects of your PC and how you can use them to influence the story.</span></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;border-bottom:solid #b45f06 1pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;padding:0pt 0pt 2pt 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#b45f06;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your Player Character</span></h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">There are three rules you must follow when you make decisions for your PC. Also, your PC has an identity, a goal, connections, and a flaw, all of which will help you follow these rules.</span></p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your PC is a unique individual in the setting.</span></h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Always keep in mind your PC’s identity. You are not your PC, and they will often make decisions that you yourself would not make, even in the exact same situation. They have lived in the GM’s world for their entire life, and have traditions and knowledge that you do not. However, they are still your PC, and the way their identity and flaw interact with your own personality can be very exciting for everyone in the campaign.</span></p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your PC is a character in the story.</span></h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">All stories have changes and developments in them. Expect your PC to experience challenges and setbacks of varying difficulty. Use your PC’s flaw to create dramatic tension in the story, even if it is detrimental to the party’s overall objectives. The best stories are those in which a character’s flaw is a hindrance to their goal, but they overcome that flaw and finally accomplish the goal. </span></p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your PC is a member of the party.</span></h3>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-30425c0a-7fff-50de-f763-cbb362452ce7\"></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your PC’s connections tie them both to the world and to the other players at the table. Use these ties to make your PC feel grounded and realistic, as described above. However, unlike most stories written by a single author or director, Volition involves multiple players as well as the GM contributing to the story. Therefore, it is of utmost importance that you play in a way in which everyone has fun. Every PC in the party has their own goals, but PCs should still support each other in those goals. If at any time your PC’s goal is directly opposed to another PC’s goal, one of you must either change the goal or retire the PC (see Retiring a PC). There can be tension and even conflict between PCs, but you should never attempt to kill another PC or completely deny them the opportunity to accomplish their goal.</span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.lSYdoJZO8FHSFZMh"}},"_id":"QNaFu3L5Sxtqd15s"}
{"name":"Player Character Creation","content":"<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Character Concept</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The first step in making a Volition character is to think about who they are as a person. Eventually, you will be choosing skills and calculating health dice but these qualities are imperfect representations of a realistic character. Deciding the qualities in this section will give you a good idea of who that character is, and then you can decide levels and skills based off of your answers here.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Identity</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your identity is a quick, one-sentence summary of your PC. It should be interesting, unique, and descriptive.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-abf53540-7fff-dc7d-72cb-595409d9d9ec\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Rage-fueled samurai avenger, magical historian who studies both the past and future, jester who teases corrupt nobles, or symbiotic fey spirit that can change into a tree</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Goal</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your goal is what you ultimately want to see your PC accomplish by the end of the campaign. It should be specific, tangible, and achievable. Your GM will use this to plan out the adventures that the party will go on.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Take my brother’s place as head of the household, prevent the apocalypse only I have foreseen, perform the greatest heist of the century, or restore life to the grove that I once lived in</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Connections</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your connections are living people with whom your PC has some sort of bond. You must write a name and a brief description of the relationship for each connection. Your GM will use these connections to advance the story of the adventure and tie your PC into the world they are creating. You can have as many connections as you like, but as a minimum, you must have at least one connection with each of these types of character:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Another PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A friendly NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">An enemy NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Januz Gibas, a drug dealer who grew up on the streets with me. Marcel Zebro, a former lover who killed my mentor.  Bram Kivrav, a prince who I “kidnapped” so he can enjoy life outside the palace. Qay Piy, an ancient spirit of the forest that is always watching me but whose intentions are unknown.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaw</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your flaw will make your PC feel real and make their stories more interesting. It should cause negative consequences for your character and be relevant enough to come up somewhat frequently. Choose one from the list below, and then write a sentence describing how it specifically manifests in your character. If you can’t find a good match for the idea you have, have your GM create one for you. </span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Angry: My temper, especially in battle, is uncontrollable. Cautious: If I haven’t consulted three books, cast two spells peering into the future, and considered all possible outcomes, it’s not worth doing. Carefree: A good laugh is worth any risk, even a night or two in the prison cell, especially if it’s not me in the prison cell. Fear: Technology frightens me, and those who use it cannot be trusted.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaw List</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><a style=\"text-decoration:none\" href=\"https://airtable.com/shrHyguo4F71ru00B\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#1155cc;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">https://airtable.com/shrHyguo4F71ru00B</span></a><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> </span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Complication</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws include a complication, which you can choose as a complication after a messy result from a roll (see below) or when narratively appropriate.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Experience</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws provide a method to gain experience (XP), which is described in detail below. XP earned from flaws can be applied to any skill of your choice, but you must choose when the XP is earned. </span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Additional Rules</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaws can also include special rules. They are usually some detrimental effect applied to your character or a condition related to the complication or experience. These rules are to help you roleplay your character and provide mechanical effects from good roleplay, but they are simply part of your character’s complete flaw. Feel free to lean into your flaw or skirt around it as much as you desire, even when the mechanical rules do not specifically apply.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Overcoming a Flaw</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sometimes, your character might reach a point in the story where they are no longer burdened by their flaw because they have overcome it.  This happens when your character takes an action that is directly contrary to their flaw.  Someone too trusting might finally catch someone in a lie, a greedy person might turn down material gain for a greater good, or vengeful person might finally accept that vengeance will not bring them true happiness. When both you and the GM agree that your character has overcome their flaw, you gain 1 XP in every skill you have, and then you remove your current flaw and add a new one. </span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Other Details</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The following details are important facts to decide for your PC to round out their character concept. Your GM will provide more details on appropriate options for these choices.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Name</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Species</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Homeland</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Age</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Faith</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Appearance</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Personality</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Profession</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Hobbies</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"2\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Starting Skills</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">When you create a PC, they start with six different skills of your choice, two of which start at Level 2, while the rest start at Level 1. It is recommended that you take a good mix of offensive, defensive, social, exploration, and information gathering skills, as all of these will be important. Talk with the other members of your party to make sure you have a wide variety of skills among your characters, but a bit of overlap can promote cooperation and spark friendly competition. Skills and their rules are described in more detail in the next section.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"3\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Health, Armor, Supply, Gold</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Unless you have a starting skill that says otherwise, your starting health is 6/d6/d6, your starting Armor is 0, your starting Supply is 4/4, and you start with 5 gold. The usages of these attributes is described below.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"4\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Equipment and Additional Objects</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">You start with a variety of objects in addition to your supply and gold:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">All equipment needed for starting skills</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Two objects of your choice, appropriate to your PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A level 0 artifact</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> First, if any of your starting skills require equipment to use, you start with all of those objects. For example, if you start with the Swordsmanship skill, which requires a bladed weapon, you can start with your choice of a scimitar, shortsword, longsword, greatsword, or any other bladed weapon. In addition to equipment, you start with two objects of your choice that are appropriate to your PC. Check with your GM about which objects are appropriate, as they will have the final say on what objects you can choose. Typically, these are related to your character’s backstory or personality traits, such as the broken blade of your former mentor or a treasure map that you’ve been trying to decipher for years. Finally, choose one Level 0 artifact to start with, or have your GM design one for you that is most appropriate for your character. </span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kjKPLKcIN7wJPrh0"}},"_id":"jacNePVUVpf5hrvz"}
{"_id":"jacNePVUVpf5hrvz","name":"Player Character Creation","content":"<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Character Concept</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The first step in making a Volition character is to think about who they are as a person. Eventually, you will be choosing skills and calculating health dice but these qualities are imperfect representations of a realistic character. Deciding the qualities in this section will give you a good idea of who that character is, and then you can decide levels and skills based off of your answers here.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Identity</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your identity is a quick, one-sentence summary of your PC. It should be interesting, unique, and descriptive.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-abf53540-7fff-dc7d-72cb-595409d9d9ec\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Rage-fueled samurai avenger, magical historian who studies both the past and future, jester who teases corrupt nobles, or symbiotic fey spirit that can change into a tree</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Goal</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your goal is what you ultimately want to see your PC accomplish by the end of the campaign. It should be specific, tangible, and achievable. Your GM will use this to plan out the adventures that the party will go on.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Take my brother’s place as head of the household, prevent the apocalypse only I have foreseen, perform the greatest heist of the century, or restore life to the grove that I once lived in</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Connections</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your connections are living people with whom your PC has some sort of bond. You must write a name and a brief description of the relationship for each connection. Your GM will use these connections to advance the story of the adventure and tie your PC into the world they are creating. You can have as many connections as you like, but as a minimum, you must have at least one connection with each of these types of character:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Another PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A friendly NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">An enemy NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Januz Gibas, a drug dealer who grew up on the streets with me. Marcel Zebro, a former lover who killed my mentor.  Bram Kivrav, a prince who I “kidnapped” so he can enjoy life outside the palace. Qay Piy, an ancient spirit of the forest that is always watching me but whose intentions are unknown.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaw</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your flaw will make your PC feel real and make their stories more interesting. It should cause negative consequences for your character and be relevant enough to come up somewhat frequently. Choose one from the list below, and then write a sentence describing how it specifically manifests in your character. If you can’t find a good match for the idea you have, have your GM create one for you. </span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Angry: My temper, especially in battle, is uncontrollable. Cautious: If I haven’t consulted three books, cast two spells peering into the future, and considered all possible outcomes, it’s not worth doing. Carefree: A good laugh is worth any risk, even a night or two in the prison cell, especially if it’s not me in the prison cell. Fear: Technology frightens me, and those who use it cannot be trusted.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Complication</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws include a complication, which you can choose as a complication after a messy result from a roll (see below) or when narratively appropriate.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Experience</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws provide a method to gain experience (XP), which is described in detail below. XP earned from flaws can be applied to any skill of your choice, but you must choose when the XP is earned. </span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Additional Rules</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaws can also include special rules. They are usually some detrimental effect applied to your character or a condition related to the complication or experience. These rules are to help you roleplay your character and provide mechanical effects from good roleplay, but they are simply part of your character’s complete flaw. Feel free to lean into your flaw or skirt around it as much as you desire, even when the mechanical rules do not specifically apply.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Overcoming a Flaw</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sometimes, your character might reach a point in the story where they are no longer burdened by their flaw because they have overcome it.  This happens when your character takes an action that is directly contrary to their flaw.  Someone too trusting might finally catch someone in a lie, a greedy person might turn down material gain for a greater good, or vengeful person might finally accept that vengeance will not bring them true happiness. When both you and the GM agree that your character has overcome their flaw, you gain 1 XP in every skill you have, and then you remove your current flaw and add a new one. </span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Other Details</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The following details are important facts to decide for your PC to round out their character concept. Your GM will provide more details on appropriate options for these choices.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Name</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Species</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Homeland</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Age</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Faith</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Appearance</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Personality</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Profession</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Hobbies</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"2\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Starting Skills</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">When you create a PC, they start with six different skills of your choice, two of which start at Level 2, while the rest start at Level 1. It is recommended that you take a good mix of offensive, defensive, social, exploration, and information gathering skills, as all of these will be important. Talk with the other members of your party to make sure you have a wide variety of skills among your characters, but a bit of overlap can promote cooperation and spark friendly competition. Skills and their rules are described in more detail in the next section.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"3\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Health, Armor, Supply, Gold</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Unless you have a starting skill that says otherwise, your starting health is 6/d6/d6, your starting Armor is 0, your starting Supply is 4/4, and you start with 5 gold. The usages of these attributes is described below.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"4\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Equipment and Additional Objects</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">You start with a variety of objects in addition to your supply and gold:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">All equipment needed for starting skills</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Two objects of your choice, appropriate to your PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A level 0 artifact</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> First, if any of your starting skills require equipment to use, you start with all of those objects. For example, if you start with the Swordsmanship skill, which requires a bladed weapon, you can start with your choice of a scimitar, shortsword, longsword, greatsword, or any other bladed weapon. In addition to equipment, you start with two objects of your choice that are appropriate to your PC. Check with your GM about which objects are appropriate, as they will have the final say on what objects you can choose. Typically, these are related to your character’s backstory or personality traits, such as the broken blade of your former mentor or a treasure map that you’ve been trying to decipher for years. Finally, choose one Level 0 artifact to start with, or have your GM design one for you that is most appropriate for your character. </span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kjKPLKcIN7wJPrh0"}}}
{"_id":"jacNePVUVpf5hrvz","name":"Player Character Creation","content":"<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Character Concept</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The first step in making a Volition character is to think about who they are as a person. Eventually, you will be choosing skills and calculating health dice but these qualities are imperfect representations of a realistic character. Deciding the qualities in this section will give you a good idea of who that character is, and then you can decide levels and skills based off of your answers here.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Identity</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your identity is a quick, one-sentence summary of your PC. It should be interesting, unique, and descriptive.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-abf53540-7fff-dc7d-72cb-595409d9d9ec\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Rage-fueled samurai avenger, magical historian who studies both the past and future, jester who teases corrupt nobles, or symbiotic fey spirit that can change into a tree</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Goal</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your goal is what you ultimately want to see your PC accomplish by the end of the campaign. It should be specific, tangible, and achievable. Your GM will use this to plan out the adventures that the party will go on.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Take my brother’s place as head of the household, prevent the apocalypse only I have foreseen, perform the greatest heist of the century, or restore life to the grove that I once lived in</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Connections</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your connections are living people with whom your PC has some sort of bond. You must write a name and a brief description of the relationship for each connection. Your GM will use these connections to advance the story of the adventure and tie your PC into the world they are creating. You can have as many connections as you like, but as a minimum, you must have at least one connection with each of these types of character:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Another PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A friendly NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">An enemy NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Januz Gibas, a drug dealer who grew up on the streets with me. Marcel Zebro, a former lover who killed my mentor.  Bram Kivrav, a prince who I “kidnapped” so he can enjoy life outside the palace. Qay Piy, an ancient spirit of the forest that is always watching me but whose intentions are unknown.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaw</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your flaw will make your PC feel real and make their stories more interesting. It should cause negative consequences for your character and be relevant enough to come up somewhat frequently. Choose one from the list below, and then write a sentence describing how it specifically manifests in your character. If you can’t find a good match for the idea you have, have your GM create one for you. </span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Angry: My temper, especially in battle, is uncontrollable. Cautious: If I haven’t consulted three books, cast two spells peering into the future, and considered all possible outcomes, it’s not worth doing. Carefree: A good laugh is worth any risk, even a night or two in the prison cell, especially if it’s not me in the prison cell. Fear: Technology frightens me, and those who use it cannot be trusted.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Complication</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws include a complication, which you can choose as a complication after a messy result from a roll (see below) or when narratively appropriate.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Experience</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws provide a method to gain experience (XP), which is described in detail below. XP earned from flaws can be applied to any skill of your choice, but you must choose when the XP is earned. </span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Additional Rules</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaws can also include special rules. They are usually some detrimental effect applied to your character or a condition related to the complication or experience. These rules are to help you roleplay your character and provide mechanical effects from good roleplay, but they are simply part of your character’s complete flaw. Feel free to lean into your flaw or skirt around it as much as you desire, even when the mechanical rules do not specifically apply.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Overcoming a Flaw</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sometimes, your character might reach a point in the story where they are no longer burdened by their flaw because they have overcome it.  This happens when your character takes an action that is directly contrary to their flaw.  Someone too trusting might finally catch someone in a lie, a greedy person might turn down material gain for a greater good, or vengeful person might finally accept that vengeance will not bring them true happiness. When both you and the GM agree that your character has overcome their flaw, you gain 1 XP in every skill you have, and then you remove your current flaw and add a new one. </span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Other Details</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The following details are important facts to decide for your PC to round out their character concept. Your GM will provide more details on appropriate options for these choices.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Name</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Species</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Homeland</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Age</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Faith</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Appearance</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Personality</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Profession</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Hobbies</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"2\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Starting Skills</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">When you create a PC, they start with six different skills of your choice, two of which start at Level 2, while the rest start at Level 1. It is recommended that you take a good mix of offensive, defensive, social, exploration, and information gathering skills, as all of these will be important. Talk with the other members of your party to make sure you have a wide variety of skills among your characters, but a bit of overlap can promote cooperation and spark friendly competition. Skills and their rules are described in more detail in the next section.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"3\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Health, Armor, Supply, Gold</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Unless you have a starting skill that says otherwise, your starting health is 6/d6/d6, your starting Armor is 0, your starting Supply is 4/4, and you start with 5 gold. The usages of these attributes is described below.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"4\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Equipment and Additional Objects</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">You start with a variety of objects in addition to your supply and gold:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">All equipment needed for starting skills</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Two objects of your choice, appropriate to your PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A level 0 artifact</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> First, if any of your starting skills require equipment to use, you start with all of those objects. For example, if you start with the Swordsmanship skill, which requires a bladed weapon, you can start with your choice of a scimitar, shortsword, longsword, greatsword, or any other bladed weapon. In addition to equipment, you start with two objects of your choice that are appropriate to your PC. Check with your GM about which objects are appropriate, as they will have the final say on what objects you can choose. Typically, these are related to your character’s backstory or personality traits, such as the broken blade of your former mentor or a treasure map that you’ve been trying to decipher for years. Finally, choose one Level 0 artifact to start with, or have your GM design one for you that is most appropriate for your character. </span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kjKPLKcIN7wJPrh0"}}}
{"_id":"jacNePVUVpf5hrvz","name":"Player Character Creation","content":"<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Character Concept</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The first step in making a Volition character is to think about who they are as a person. Eventually, you will be choosing skills and calculating health dice but these qualities are imperfect representations of a realistic character. Deciding the qualities in this section will give you a good idea of who that character is, and then you can decide levels and skills based off of your answers here.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Identity</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your identity is a quick, one-sentence summary of your PC. It should be interesting, unique, and descriptive.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-abf53540-7fff-dc7d-72cb-595409d9d9ec\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Rage-fueled samurai avenger, magical historian who studies both the past and future, jester who teases corrupt nobles, or symbiotic fey spirit that can change into a tree</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Goal</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your goal is what you ultimately want to see your PC accomplish by the end of the campaign. It should be specific, tangible, and achievable. Your GM will use this to plan out the adventures that the party will go on.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Take my brother’s place as head of the household, prevent the apocalypse only I have foreseen, perform the greatest heist of the century, or restore life to the grove that I once lived in</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Connections</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your connections are living people with whom your PC has some sort of bond. You must write a name and a brief description of the relationship for each connection. Your GM will use these connections to advance the story of the adventure and tie your PC into the world they are creating. You can have as many connections as you like, but as a minimum, you must have at least one connection with each of these types of character:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Another PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A friendly NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">An enemy NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Januz Gibas, a drug dealer who grew up on the streets with me. Marcel Zebro, a former lover who killed my mentor.  Bram Kivrav, a prince who I “kidnapped” so he can enjoy life outside the palace. Qay Piy, an ancient spirit of the forest that is always watching me but whose intentions are unknown.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaw</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your flaw will make your PC feel real and make their stories more interesting. It should cause negative consequences for your character and be relevant enough to come up somewhat frequently. Choose one from the list below, and then write a sentence describing how it specifically manifests in your character. If you can’t find a good match for the idea you have, have your GM create one for you. </span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Angry: My temper, especially in battle, is uncontrollable. Cautious: If I haven’t consulted three books, cast two spells peering into the future, and considered all possible outcomes, it’s not worth doing. Carefree: A good laugh is worth any risk, even a night or two in the prison cell, especially if it’s not me in the prison cell. Fear: Technology frightens me, and those who use it cannot be trusted.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Complication</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws include a complication, which you can choose as a complication after a messy result from a roll (see below) or when narratively appropriate.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Experience</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws provide a method to gain experience (XP), which is described in detail below. XP earned from flaws can be applied to any skill of your choice, but you must choose when the XP is earned. </span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Additional Rules</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaws can also include special rules. They are usually some detrimental effect applied to your character or a condition related to the complication or experience. These rules are to help you roleplay your character and provide mechanical effects from good roleplay, but they are simply part of your character’s complete flaw. Feel free to lean into your flaw or skirt around it as much as you desire, even when the mechanical rules do not specifically apply.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Overcoming a Flaw</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sometimes, your character might reach a point in the story where they are no longer burdened by their flaw because they have overcome it.  This happens when your character takes an action that is directly contrary to their flaw.  Someone too trusting might finally catch someone in a lie, a greedy person might turn down material gain for a greater good, or vengeful person might finally accept that vengeance will not bring them true happiness. When both you and the GM agree that your character has overcome their flaw, you gain 1 XP in every skill you have, and then you remove your current flaw and add a new one. </span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Other Details</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The following details are important facts to decide for your PC to round out their character concept. Your GM will provide more details on appropriate options for these choices.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Name</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Species</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Homeland</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Age</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Faith</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Appearance</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Personality</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Profession</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Hobbies</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"2\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Starting Skills</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">When you create a PC, they start with six different skills of your choice, two of which start at Level 2, while the rest start at Level 1. It is recommended that you take a good mix of offensive, defensive, social, exploration, and information gathering skills, as all of these will be important. Talk with the other members of your party to make sure you have a wide variety of skills among your characters, but a bit of overlap can promote cooperation and spark friendly competition. Skills and their rules are described in more detail in the next section.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"3\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Health, Armor, Supply, Gold</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Unless you have a starting skill that says otherwise, your starting health is 6/d6/d6, your starting Armor is 0, your starting Supply is 4/4, and you start with 5 gold. The usages of these attributes is described below.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"4\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Equipment and Additional Objects</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">You start with a variety of objects in addition to your supply and gold:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">All equipment needed for starting skills</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Two objects of your choice, appropriate to your PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A level 0 artifact</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> First, if any of your starting skills require equipment to use, you start with all of those objects. For example, if you start with the Swordsmanship skill, which requires a bladed weapon, you can start with your choice of a scimitar, shortsword, longsword, greatsword, or any other bladed weapon. In addition to equipment, you start with two objects of your choice that are appropriate to your PC. Check with your GM about which objects are appropriate, as they will have the final say on what objects you can choose. Typically, these are related to your character’s backstory or personality traits, such as the broken blade of your former mentor or a treasure map that you’ve been trying to decipher for years. Finally, choose one Level 0 artifact to start with, or have your GM design one for you that is most appropriate for your character. </span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kjKPLKcIN7wJPrh0"}}}
{"_id":"jacNePVUVpf5hrvz","name":"Player Character Creation","content":"<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Character Concept</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The first step in making a Volition character is to think about who they are as a person. Eventually, you will be choosing skills and calculating health dice but these qualities are imperfect representations of a realistic character. Deciding the qualities in this section will give you a good idea of who that character is, and then you can decide levels and skills based off of your answers here.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Identity</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your identity is a quick, one-sentence summary of your PC. It should be interesting, unique, and descriptive.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-abf53540-7fff-dc7d-72cb-595409d9d9ec\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Rage-fueled samurai avenger, magical historian who studies both the past and future, jester who teases corrupt nobles, or symbiotic fey spirit that can change into a tree</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Goal</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your goal is what you ultimately want to see your PC accomplish by the end of the campaign. It should be specific, tangible, and achievable. Your GM will use this to plan out the adventures that the party will go on.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Take my brother’s place as head of the household, prevent the apocalypse only I have foreseen, perform the greatest heist of the century, or restore life to the grove that I once lived in</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Connections</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your connections are living people with whom your PC has some sort of bond. You must write a name and a brief description of the relationship for each connection. Your GM will use these connections to advance the story of the adventure and tie your PC into the world they are creating. You can have as many connections as you like, but as a minimum, you must have at least one connection with each of these types of character:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Another PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A friendly NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">An enemy NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Januz Gibas, a drug dealer who grew up on the streets with me. Marcel Zebro, a former lover who killed my mentor.  Bram Kivrav, a prince who I “kidnapped” so he can enjoy life outside the palace. Qay Piy, an ancient spirit of the forest that is always watching me but whose intentions are unknown.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaw</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your flaw will make your PC feel real and make their stories more interesting. It should cause negative consequences for your character and be relevant enough to come up somewhat frequently. Choose one from the list below, and then write a sentence describing how it specifically manifests in your character. If you can’t find a good match for the idea you have, have your GM create one for you. </span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Angry: My temper, especially in battle, is uncontrollable. Cautious: If I haven’t consulted three books, cast two spells peering into the future, and considered all possible outcomes, it’s not worth doing. Carefree: A good laugh is worth any risk, even a night or two in the prison cell, especially if it’s not me in the prison cell. Fear: Technology frightens me, and those who use it cannot be trusted.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Complication</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws include a complication, which you can choose as a complication after a messy result from a roll (see below) or when narratively appropriate.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Experience</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws provide a method to gain experience (XP), which is described in detail below. XP earned from flaws can be applied to any skill of your choice, but you must choose when the XP is earned. </span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Additional Rules</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaws can also include special rules. They are usually some detrimental effect applied to your character or a condition related to the complication or experience. These rules are to help you roleplay your character and provide mechanical effects from good roleplay, but they are simply part of your character’s complete flaw. Feel free to lean into your flaw or skirt around it as much as you desire, even when the mechanical rules do not specifically apply.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Overcoming a Flaw</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sometimes, your character might reach a point in the story where they are no longer burdened by their flaw because they have overcome it.  This happens when your character takes an action that is directly contrary to their flaw.  Someone too trusting might finally catch someone in a lie, a greedy person might turn down material gain for a greater good, or vengeful person might finally accept that vengeance will not bring them true happiness. When both you and the GM agree that your character has overcome their flaw, you gain 1 XP in every skill you have, and then you remove your current flaw and add a new one. </span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Other Details</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The following details are important facts to decide for your PC to round out their character concept. Your GM will provide more details on appropriate options for these choices.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Name</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Species</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Homeland</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Age</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Faith</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Appearance</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Personality</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Profession</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Hobbies</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"2\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Starting Skills</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">When you create a PC, they start with six different skills of your choice, two of which start at Level 2, while the rest start at Level 1. It is recommended that you take a good mix of offensive, defensive, social, exploration, and information gathering skills, as all of these will be important. Talk with the other members of your party to make sure you have a wide variety of skills among your characters, but a bit of overlap can promote cooperation and spark friendly competition. Skills and their rules are described in more detail in the next section.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"3\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Health, Armor, Supply, Gold</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Unless you have a starting skill that says otherwise, your starting health is 6/d6/d6, your starting Armor is 0, your starting Supply is 4/4, and you start with 5 gold. The usages of these attributes is described below.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"4\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Equipment and Additional Objects</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">You start with a variety of objects in addition to your supply and gold:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">All equipment needed for starting skills</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Two objects of your choice, appropriate to your PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A level 0 artifact</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> First, if any of your starting skills require equipment to use, you start with all of those objects. For example, if you start with the Swordsmanship skill, which requires a bladed weapon, you can start with your choice of a scimitar, shortsword, longsword, greatsword, or any other bladed weapon. In addition to equipment, you start with two objects of your choice that are appropriate to your PC. Check with your GM about which objects are appropriate, as they will have the final say on what objects you can choose. Typically, these are related to your character’s backstory or personality traits, such as the broken blade of your former mentor or a treasure map that you’ve been trying to decipher for years. Finally, choose one Level 0 artifact to start with, or have your GM design one for you that is most appropriate for your character. </span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kjKPLKcIN7wJPrh0"}}}
{"_id":"jacNePVUVpf5hrvz","name":"Player Character Creation","content":"<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Character Concept</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The first step in making a Volition character is to think about who they are as a person. Eventually, you will be choosing skills and calculating health dice but these qualities are imperfect representations of a realistic character. Deciding the qualities in this section will give you a good idea of who that character is, and then you can decide levels and skills based off of your answers here.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Identity</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your identity is a quick, one-sentence summary of your PC. It should be interesting, unique, and descriptive.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-abf53540-7fff-dc7d-72cb-595409d9d9ec\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Rage-fueled samurai avenger, magical historian who studies both the past and future, jester who teases corrupt nobles, or symbiotic fey spirit that can change into a tree</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Goal</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your goal is what you ultimately want to see your PC accomplish by the end of the campaign. It should be specific, tangible, and achievable. Your GM will use this to plan out the adventures that the party will go on.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples: </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Take my brother’s place as head of the household, prevent the apocalypse only I have foreseen, perform the greatest heist of the century, or restore life to the grove that I once lived in</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Connections</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your connections are living people with whom your PC has some sort of bond. You must write a name and a brief description of the relationship for each connection. Your GM will use these connections to advance the story of the adventure and tie your PC into the world they are creating. You can have as many connections as you like, but as a minimum, you must have at least one connection with each of these types of character:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Another PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A friendly NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">An enemy NPC</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Januz Gibas, a drug dealer who grew up on the streets with me. Marcel Zebro, a former lover who killed my mentor.  Bram Kivrav, a prince who I “kidnapped” so he can enjoy life outside the palace. Qay Piy, an ancient spirit of the forest that is always watching me but whose intentions are unknown.</span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaw</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Your flaw will make your PC feel real and make their stories more interesting. It should cause negative consequences for your character and be relevant enough to come up somewhat frequently. Choose one from the list below, and then write a sentence describing how it specifically manifests in your character. If you can’t find a good match for the idea you have, have your GM create one for you. </span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Examples:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Angry: My temper, especially in battle, is uncontrollable. Cautious: If I haven’t consulted three books, cast two spells peering into the future, and considered all possible outcomes, it’s not worth doing. Carefree: A good laugh is worth any risk, even a night or two in the prison cell, especially if it’s not me in the prison cell. Fear: Technology frightens me, and those who use it cannot be trusted.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Complication</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws include a complication, which you can choose as a complication after a messy result from a roll (see below) or when narratively appropriate.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Experience</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Some flaws provide a method to gain experience (XP), which is described in detail below. XP earned from flaws can be applied to any skill of your choice, but you must choose when the XP is earned. </span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Additional Rules</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Flaws can also include special rules. They are usually some detrimental effect applied to your character or a condition related to the complication or experience. These rules are to help you roleplay your character and provide mechanical effects from good roleplay, but they are simply part of your character’s complete flaw. Feel free to lean into your flaw or skirt around it as much as you desire, even when the mechanical rules do not specifically apply.</span></p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#666666;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Overcoming a Flaw</span></h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sometimes, your character might reach a point in the story where they are no longer burdened by their flaw because they have overcome it.  This happens when your character takes an action that is directly contrary to their flaw.  Someone too trusting might finally catch someone in a lie, a greedy person might turn down material gain for a greater good, or vengeful person might finally accept that vengeance will not bring them true happiness. When both you and the GM agree that your character has overcome their flaw, you gain 1 XP in every skill you have, and then you remove your current flaw and add a new one. </span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#e69138;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Other Details</span></h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The following details are important facts to decide for your PC to round out their character concept. Your GM will provide more details on appropriate options for these choices.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Name</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Species</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Homeland</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Age</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Faith</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Appearance</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Personality</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Profession</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Hobbies</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"2\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Starting Skills</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">When you create a PC, they start with six different skills of your choice, two of which start at Level 2, while the rest start at Level 1. It is recommended that you take a good mix of offensive, defensive, social, exploration, and information gathering skills, as all of these will be important. Talk with the other members of your party to make sure you have a wide variety of skills among your characters, but a bit of overlap can promote cooperation and spark friendly competition. Skills and their rules are described in more detail in the next section.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"3\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Health, Armor, Supply, Gold</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Unless you have a starting skill that says otherwise, your starting health is 6/d6/d6, your starting Armor is 0, your starting Supply is 4/4, and you start with 5 gold. The usages of these attributes is described below.</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\" start=\"4\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:16pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#bf9000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Equipment and Additional Objects</span></h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">You start with a variety of objects in addition to your supply and gold:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">All equipment needed for starting skills</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Two objects of your choice, appropriate to your PC</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">A level 0 artifact</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:'Century Gothic',sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> First, if any of your starting skills require equipment to use, you start with all of those objects. For example, if you start with the Swordsmanship skill, which requires a bladed weapon, you can start with your choice of a scimitar, shortsword, longsword, greatsword, or any other bladed weapon. In addition to equipment, you start with two objects of your choice that are appropriate to your PC. Check with your GM about which objects are appropriate, as they will have the final say on what objects you can choose. Typically, these are related to your character’s backstory or personality traits, such as the broken blade of your former mentor or a treasure map that you’ve been trying to decipher for years. Finally, choose one Level 0 artifact to start with, or have your GM design one for you that is most appropriate for your character. </span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kjKPLKcIN7wJPrh0"}}}
{"_id":"jacNePVUVpf5hrvz","name":"Player Character Creation","content":"<ol>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Character Concept</h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The first step in making a Volition character is to think about who they are as a person. Eventually, you will be choosing skills and calculating health dice but these qualities are imperfect representations of a realistic character. Deciding the qualities in this section will give you a good idea of who that character is, and then you can decide levels and skills based off of your answers here.</p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\">Identity</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Your identity is a quick, one-sentence summary of your PC. It should be interesting, unique, and descriptive.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Examples: Rage-fueled samurai avenger, magical historian who studies both the past and future, jester who teases corrupt nobles, or symbiotic fey spirit that can change into a tree</p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\">Goal</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Your goal is what you ultimately want to see your PC accomplish by the end of the campaign. It should be specific, tangible, and achievable. Your GM will use this to plan out the adventures that the party will go on.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Examples: Take my brother’s place as head of the household, prevent the apocalypse only I have foreseen, perform the greatest heist of the century, or restore life to the grove that I once lived in</p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\">Connections</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Your connections are living people with whom your PC has some sort of bond. You must write a name and a brief description of the relationship for each connection. Your GM will use these connections to advance the story of the adventure and tie your PC into the world they are creating. You can have as many connections as you like, but as a minimum, you must have at least one connection with each of these types of character:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Another PC</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A friendly NPC</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">An enemy NPC</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Examples: Januz Gibas, a drug dealer who grew up on the streets with me. Marcel Zebro, a former lover who killed my mentor.  Bram Kivrav, a prince who I “kidnapped” so he can enjoy life outside the palace. Qay Piy, an ancient spirit of the forest that is always watching me but whose intentions are unknown.</p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\">Flaw</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Your flaw will make your PC feel real and make their stories more interesting. It should cause negative consequences for your character and be relevant enough to come up somewhat frequently. Choose one from the list below, and then write a sentence describing how it specifically manifests in your character. If you can’t find a good match for the idea you have, have your GM create one for you. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Examples: Angry: My temper, especially in battle, is uncontrollable. Cautious: If I haven’t consulted three books, cast two spells peering into the future, and considered all possible outcomes, it’s not worth doing. Carefree: A good laugh is worth any risk, even a night or two in the prison cell, especially if it’s not me in the prison cell. Fear: Technology frightens me, and those who use it cannot be trusted.</p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\">Complication</h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Some flaws include a complication, which you can choose as a complication after a messy result from a roll (see below) or when narratively appropriate.</p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\">Experience</h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Some flaws provide a method to gain experience (XP), which is described in detail below. XP earned from flaws can be applied to any skill of your choice, but you must choose when the XP is earned. </p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\">Additional Rules</h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Flaws can also include special rules. They are usually some detrimental effect applied to your character or a condition related to the complication or experience. These rules are to help you roleplay your character and provide mechanical effects from good roleplay, but they are simply part of your character’s complete flaw. Feel free to lean into your flaw or skirt around it as much as you desire, even when the mechanical rules do not specifically apply.</p>\n<h5 dir=\"ltr\">Overcoming a Flaw</h5>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Sometimes, your character might reach a point in the story where they are no longer burdened by their flaw because they have overcome it.  This happens when your character takes an action that is directly contrary to their flaw.  Someone too trusting might finally catch someone in a lie, a greedy person might turn down material gain for a greater good, or vengeful person might finally accept that vengeance will not bring them true happiness. When both you and the GM agree that your character has overcome their flaw, you gain 1 XP in every skill you have, and then you remove your current flaw and add a new one. </p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\">Other Details</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The following details are important facts to decide for your PC to round out their character concept. Your GM will provide more details on appropriate options for these choices.</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Name</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Species</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Homeland</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Age</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Faith</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Appearance</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Personality</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Profession</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Hobbies</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Starting Skills</h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">When you create a PC, they start with six different skills of your choice, two of which start at Level 2, while the rest start at Level 1. It is recommended that you take a good mix of offensive, defensive, social, exploration, and information gathering skills, as all of these will be important. Talk with the other members of your party to make sure you have a wide variety of skills among your characters, but a bit of overlap can promote cooperation and spark friendly competition. Skills and their rules are described in more detail in the next section.</p>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Health, Armor, Supply, Gold</h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unless you have a starting skill that says otherwise, your starting health is 6/d6/d6, your starting Armor is 0, your starting Supply is 4/4, and you start with 5 gold. The usages of these attributes is described below.</p>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Equipment and Additional Objects</h3>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You start with a variety of objects in addition to your supply and gold:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">All equipment needed for starting skills</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Two objects of your choice, appropriate to your PC</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A level 0 artifact</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> First, if any of your starting skills require equipment to use, you start with all of those objects. For example, if you start with the Swordsmanship skill, which requires a bladed weapon, you can start with your choice of a scimitar, shortsword, longsword, greatsword, or any other bladed weapon. In addition to equipment, you start with two objects of your choice that are appropriate to your PC. Check with your GM about which objects are appropriate, as they will have the final say on what objects you can choose. Typically, these are related to your character’s backstory or personality traits, such as the broken blade of your former mentor or a treasure map that you’ve been trying to decipher for years. Finally, choose one Level 0 artifact to start with, or have your GM design one for you that is most appropriate for your character. </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kjKPLKcIN7wJPrh0"}}}
