rt at Level 1. It is recommended that you take a good mix of offensive, defensive, social, exploration, and information gathering skills, as all of these will be important. Talk with the other members of your party to make sure you have a wide variety of skills among your characters, but a bit of overlap can promote cooperation and spark friendly competition. Skills and their rules are described in more detail in the next section.</p>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\">Health, Armor, Supply, Gold</h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unless you have a starting skill that says otherwise, your starting health is 6/d6/d6, your starting Armor is 0, your starting Supply is 4/4, and you start with 5 gold. The usages of these attributes is described below.</p>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\">Equipment and Additional Objects</h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You start with a variety of objects in addition to your supply and gold:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">All equipment needed for starting skills</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Two objects of your choice, appropriate to your PC</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A level 0 artifact</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> First, if any of your starting skills require equipment to use, you start with all of those objects. For example, if you start with the Swordsmanship skill, which requires a bladed weapon, you can start with your choice of a scimitar, shortsword, longsword, greatsword, or any other bladed weapon. In addition to equipment, you start with two objects of your choice that are appropriate to your PC. Check with your GM about which objects are appropriate, as they will have the final say on what objects you can choose. Typically, these are related to your character’s backstory or personality traits, such as the broken blade of your former mentor or a treasure map that you’ve been trying to decipher for years. Finally, choose one Level 0 artifact to start with, or have your GM design one for you that is most appropriate for your character. </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XiploJ9JSc5wv71U":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kjKPLKcIN7wJPrh0"}}}
